					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up in front of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>1619 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year Sidhārthi, Kārttīka. śu. 15. The date of the record is corresponding to Śaka year 1541 = 1619 A.D. November 11, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>Registers an agreement <hi rend="italic">(kavulu)</hi> made between the Kāpulu and <hi rend="italic">mahā maṇḍalēśvara</hi> Komāra Rāmarājayya, the son of Pōṭipāṭi Komāra Timmarājayadēva mahārāja, to plough and spouting the seed <hi rend="italic">(bijāvani)</hi> in the field called <hi rend="italic">rēgaḍubīḍu</hi> situated at Kuṁkanūru, with an agreement to pay the fees at the rate (?) of Vaga 3 in the third year total cost of 7 <hi rend="italic">maḍas</hi> for whole three years to the Kāmpus.</p>						

						</summary>
